The paper deals with a problem of assigning tasks to agents over multiple cycles, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence and optimization (cs.AI). The problem involves maximizing profit while maintaining diversity, which is a typical optimization problem (cs.DS). The paper proposes a method for solving the problem using a General Assignment Problem, which is a common technique in optimization and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the applicability of the method to different domains, which suggests a broad scope of the research (cs.RO). Finally, the paper presents a real-world case study from the software engineering domain, which suggests a possible connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
